    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_fyssyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fyssyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>fyst</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>finsun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>finst</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>писать</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>write</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fyssæg</orth></form>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>finsæg</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>писатель</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>writer</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Xetæg padcax Vaxtangmæ ḱīnyg nyffysta; fyssy jæm: „Calynmæ Xetæg
                            ægas wa, walynmæ… dæwmæ nīḱʼī bawændʒæn“</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Хетаг написал письмо царю Вахтангу; пишет ему: «Пока Хетаг жив, никто
                                не осмелится (пойти) на тебя»</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Khetag wrote a letter to King Vakhtang; he wrote to him: “While
                                Khetag is alive, no one will dare to attack you”</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>232</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>wæd Xsærtæg afysta gæxxæt jæ fynæj ævsymærmæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>тогда Хсартаг написал бумажку к своему спящему брату</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>then Khsartag wrote a piece of paper to his sleeping brother</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>finsʒinan kæʒos æma ræsuǧd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мы будем писать чисто и красиво</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>we will write in a clean and beautiful way</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>I 3</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>tabu xucawæn, e ci sfinsa, ci stærxon kæna e xwarz</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>славословие богу, что он предназначит („напишет“), как он рассудит,
                                так и хорошо</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>praise to God, what he intends (“writes”), how he is judging, so it
                                will be good</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"
                            /><biblScope>21</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>nyxy fyst</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">судьба</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q rendition="rend_singlequotes">destiny</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> („написанное на лбу“)</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (“written on a forehead”)</note>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>iræzgæ cæwuncæ næwæg finsgutæ, næwæg nivgængutæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>растут новые писатели, новые художники</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>new writers, new artists are growing</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"
                            /><biblScope>292%l2%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Общеиндоевропейское слово. Древнейшее значение было „делать
                    надрезы, наносить знаки, орнамент, узор“. Это значение ясно выступает в таких
                    выражениях, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ḱʼīrī"/>-%ifyssæn%i ‘деревянная
                    формочка, с помощью которой наносится рисунок на печенье (<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ḱʼīrī"/>)’, %iǵippæj-fyst%i ‘ситец’, буквально „(ткань)
                    разрисованная (%ifyst%i) путем печатания (%iǵippæj%i, см. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ǵīpp"/>)“. Индоевропейские языки дают два вида основы: с
                    носовым инфиксом и без него (*%ipinḱ-%i и %i*piḱ-%i, %ipins-%i и %ipis-%i).
                    Осетинский (%ifins-%i) отражает первый вариант; иронское %ifyssyn%i — из
                    %i*fynsyn%i в результате ассимиляции %ins%i → %iss%i, как в ряде других случаев:
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_yssæʒ"/> | %iinsæj%i, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_tʼyssyn"/> | %itʼunsun%i, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_yssyn"/> | %iinsun%i и др. (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>380</biblScope></bibl>). Ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>nivištan : nivīs-</w></mentioned> (= ос. %inyffyssyn%i), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="oru"><lang/>
                        <w>pis-</w>
                        <gloss><q>писать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"
                            ><w>pištak</w>
                        <gloss><q>написанный</q></gloss></mentioned>,<note type="footnote" n="1">
                        PUT NOTE HERE </note>
                    <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*nipes-(npʼys-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>писать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>*nipesak(npʼysʼk)</w>
                        <gloss><q>пишущий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>pyšt</w>
                        <gloss><q>написанный</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope>XXIX 105 сл.</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>paes-</w>
                        <gloss><q>украшать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>zaranyō-paesa-, zaranyo-pis-</w>
                        <gloss><q>украшенный золотом</q></gloss></mentioned> (=ос. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_zærīn"/>-%ifyst%i), <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>pišta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>украшенный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                            ><w>niyapišam</w>
                        <gloss><q>я написал</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                            ><w>nipištanaiy</w>
                        <gloss><q>написать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                            ><w>nipišta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>написанный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pins-</w>
                        <gloss><q>украшать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>pisati</w>
                        <gloss><q>он украшает</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">пьсати</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>писать</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">пьстръ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>пёстрый</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>pёszti</w>
                        <gloss><q>чертить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>писать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"
                            ><w>paīszinti</w>
                        <gloss><q>мазать сажей</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>feh</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>ποικίλος</w>
                        <gloss><q>пестрый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>pingo</w>
                        <gloss><q>рисую</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>раскрашиваю</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/>
                        <w>pink-, paik-</w>
                        <gloss><q>писать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-tchr"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>рисовать</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ос. %ifyst%i = <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>pyšt-</w></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>pišta-</w></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>pictus</w></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 55</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>18,
                            63</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>66</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>24, 26,
                            69</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Common Indo-European word. The most ancient meaning was “to make
                    cuts, to apply signs, ornament, pattern”. This meaning appears clearly in
                    expressions such as <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ḱʼīrī"/>-%ifyssæn%i ‘a wooden
                    mold with which a pattern is applied to cookies (<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ḱʼīrī"/>)’, %iǵippæj-fyst%i ‘printed cotton’, literally
                    „(fabric) painted (%ifyst%i) by printing (%iǵippæj%i, see <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_ǵīpp"/>)“. Indo-European languages give two types of stems:
                    with and without nasal infix (*%ipinḱ-%i and %i*piḱ-%i, %ipins-%i and %ipis-%i).
                    Ossetic (%ifins-%i) reflects the first variant; Iron %ifyssyn%i is from
                    %i*fynsyn%i as the result of assimilation %ins%i → %iss%i, as in some other
                    cases: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_yssæʒ"/> | %iinsæj%i, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_tʼyssyn"/> | %itʼunsun%i, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_yssyn"/> | %iinsun%i etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>380</biblScope></bibl>). Compare with
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>nivištan : nivīs-</w></mentioned> (= Ossetic %inyffyssyn%i), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="oru"><lang/>
                        <w>pis-</w>
                        <gloss><q>write</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"
                            ><w>pištak</w>
                        <gloss><q>written</q></gloss></mentioned>,<note type="footnote" n="1"> PUT
                        NOTE HERE </note>
                    <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*nipes-(npʼys-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>write</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>*nipesak(npʼysʼk)</w>
                        <gloss><q>writing</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>pyšt</w>
                        <gloss><q>written</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">XXIX 105
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">XXIX 105
                    ff.</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>paes-</w>
                        <gloss><q>decorate</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>zaranyō-paesa-, zaranyo-pis-</w>
                        <gloss><q>decorated with gold</q></gloss></mentioned> (= Ossetic <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_zærīn"/>-%ifyst%i), <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>pišta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>decorated</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                            ><w>niyapišam</w>
                        <gloss><q>I wrote</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                            ><w>nipištanaiy</w>
                        <gloss><q>write</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                            ><w>nipišta-</w>
                        <gloss><q>written</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pins-</w>
                        <gloss><q>decorate</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w>pisati</w>
                        <gloss><q>he is decorating</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>pьsati</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>pisatʼ</w>
                        <gloss><q>write</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>pьstrъ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>pëstryj</w>
                        <gloss><q>multicoloured</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>pёszti</w>
                        <gloss><q>draw</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>write</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"
                            ><w>paīszinti</w>
                        <gloss><q>cover with soot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>feh</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>ποικίλος</w>
                        <gloss><q>multicoloured</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>pingo</w>
                        <gloss><q>I am drawing</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>I am colouring</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/>
                        <w>pink-, paik-</w>
                        <gloss><q>write</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-tchr"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>draw</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ossetic %ifyst%i = <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>pyšt-</w></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>pišta-</w></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>pictus</w></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 55</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>18,
                            63</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>66</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>24, 26,
                            69</biblScope></bibl>., ( (), , , , , ,</etym>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="ru" n="1">Прочие новоиранские формы примыкают к
                        персидскому:<mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>nəvīsin</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>nibīsag</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>nəwis- : nəwišt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>naviš- : nəvišt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>nəviš- : nəvišt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>nuviš-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>nəviš-</w></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>növīš</w></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Зарубин</author></bibl>). В отличие
                    от них осетинская форма является оригинальной.</note>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="en" n="1">Other New Iranian forms are adjacent to
                    Persian: <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>nəvīsin</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>nibīsag</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>nəwis- : nəwišt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/>
                        <w>naviš- : nəvišt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>nəviš- : nəvišt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>nuviš-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>nəviš-</w></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Morgenstierne</author></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>növīš</w></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Zarubin</author></bibl>). In
                    contrast, the Ossetian form is original.</note>
            </entry>
